{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Make 1 batch quick puff pastry (see page XX) and marzipan (see page XX).","Preheat oven to 180°C and line 2 large baking trays with baking paper.","Place pistachios, almonds and sugar in mixing bowl then chop <b>3-4 sec\/speed 5<b>. Transfer to a small bowl and set aside.","Cut chilled pastry in half then, on a lightly floured surface, roll each piece into a square (approx. 30 cm x 30 cm).","Roll out marzipan to same size as one piece of pastry.","Brush one square of pastry with beaten egg then sprinkle over  ⅓ reserved nut mixture. Lay rolled out marzipan over nuts then brush with reserved beaten egg. Sprinkle with ⅓  reserved nut mixture.","Lay second square of pastry on top of marzipan layer, brush with reserved beaten egg, then trim edges to form a neat square (28 cm x 28 cm).","Cut square into 8 strips, 3.5 cm wide. Twist each strip 3 to 4 times, then transfer to prepared baking trays. Brush for a final time with reserved beaten egg then scatter over remaining nut mixture.","Bake for 15-18 minutes (180°C) until puffed and golden. Leave to cool for 5 minutes then transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.","Serve dusted with icing sugar."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["490 g quick puff pastry, homemade (1 batch)","250 g marzipan, homemade","30 g pistachio nuts, unsalted","30 g blanched almonds","30 g light brown sugar","plain flour, for dusting","1 medium egg, beaten","1 Tbsp icing sugar, for dusting"]}],"id":"r132991","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-Q3INhLt9CTQ\/XZWq6ipeKYI\/AAAAAAAAffQ\/a-bG4zlkc3AzHxoGKXzql74i7k6zotMGgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_YQnzvhRkoafryvBo.png","title":"Pistachio Almond Twists","publishedAt":"2017-11-24T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"8.3 g","fat":"64.8 g","uom":"per 1 piece","carbohydrates":"42.7 g","calories":"3294 kJ \/ 787 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 large baking trays, baking paper, rolling pin, long sharp knife, pastry brush, wire rack, oven","basicInfo":["medium"